'''University Hospital Center Dr Dragi<U+0161>a Mi<U+0161>ovi<U+0107>''' (sometimes Clinical Hospital Center Dr Dragi<U+0161>a Mi<U+0161>ovi<U+0107><U+2013>Dedinje; {{lang-sr|<U+041A><U+043B><U+0438><U+043D><U+0438><U+0447><U+043A><U+043E>-<U+0431><U+043E><U+043B><U+043D><U+0438><U+0447><U+043A><U+0438> <U+0446><U+0435><U+043D><U+0442><U+0430><U+0440> <U+0414><U+0440> <U+0414><U+0440><U+0430><U+0433><U+0438><U+0448><U+0430> <U+041C><U+0438><U+0448><U+043E><U+0432><U+0438><U+045B>-<U+0414><U+0435><U+0434><U+0438><U+045A><U+0435>, ''Klini<U+010D>ko<U+2013>bolni<U+010D>ki centar Dr Dragi<U+0161>a Mi<U+0161>ovi<U+0107><U+2013>Dedinje''}}) is a health facility of [[Health care#Secondary Care|secondary level]] in [[Belgrade]], that performs specialist health care in its hospitals and clinics. This medical institution is based on modern principles of [[health care]].<ref name="about us-vm">[http://www.dragisamisovic.bg.ac.rs/stranice/a_onama_misija.html ''Vizija i misija''].''DragisaMisovic.bg.ac.rs'' '''KBC Dr Dragi<U+0161>a Mi<U+0161>ovi<U+0107>'''.</ref> It is teaching facility of [[University of Belgrade School of Medicine]].<ref name="about us-vm" /> It was established in 1930.

This Institution is named by [[Dragi<U+0161>a Mi<U+0161>ovi<U+0107>]], pre<U+2013>[[World War II|WWII]] [[Communism|communist]] and [[Physician|doctor]].

On 24 October 2009 a great fire accident occurred in central building of the Hospital Center,<ref name="novosti">{{cite journal|last=Janjatovic |first=Petar|date=24 October 2009|title=Od vatre spaseno svih 300 pacijenata|publisher=Novosti|url=http://www.novosti.rs/vesti/naslovna/aktuelno.69.html:255061-Od-vatre-spaseno---svih-300-pacijenata|accessdate=29 August 2011}}</ref><ref name="press">{{cite journal|last=D|first=S|date=25 October 2009|title=Drama na Dedinju: Veliki po<U+017E>ar u KBC <U+2018>Dragi<U+0161>a Mi<U+0161>ovi<U+0107><U+2019>|publisher=Press |url=http://www.pressonline.rs/sr/vesti/vesti_dana/story/84378/Drama+na+Dedinju%3A+Veliki+po%C5%BEar+u+KBC+%E2%80%9EDragi%C5%A1a+Mi%C5%A1ovi%C4%87%22.html|accessdate=29 August 2011}}</ref><ref name="about us-vm" /> which interrupted a lot future operating of the center. Regardless, the main services are still active in emerged circumstances.<ref name="about us-vm" />

== History ==
History of Dr Dragi<U+0161>a Mi<U+0161>ovi<U+0107> Complex begins with 1920s. Former Society of Young Women Doctors gained a place near Dedinje from [[<U+0110>or<U+0111>e Vajfert|Georg Weifert]].<ref name="about us-vm" /> In 1930, by architectural design of <U+017D>ivan Nikoli<U+0107>, was built an object designed for Belgrade mistress' rest (today's Children Hospital for Pulmonary Diseases and [[Tuberculosis]]).

